## 6.2.2 Applying Causal Inference to Trading

### Purpose

Explain the practical workflow for applying causal inference in trading systems.

### Setup / formulation

Causal inference is applied in four steps:

- Document causal assumptions in the trading system.
- Articulate counterfactuals.
- Estimate counterfactuals under the causal assumptions.
- Communicate causal assumptions and counterfactuals to stakeholders.

Causal graphs can also define simulation data-generating processes.

### Main result

A causal model can serve both as:

- An estimation framework for historical data.
- A simulation framework for experiments and system design.

### Interpretation

The same graph can coordinate researchers, traders, and developers. It clarifies which actions the system can take, which quantities can be measured, and which assumptions support the resulting estimates.

