## 6.6.2 Actions and Counterfactuals

### Purpose

State the key counterfactuals under the time-aware graph.

### Setup / formulation

The chapter defines three counterfactuals.

Follow-up impact counterfactual:

$$
p(\Delta P_2 \mid do(Q_2), do(Q_1=0)).
$$

Alpha autocorrelation counterfactual:

$$
p(\alpha_2 \mid do(\alpha_1=0)).
$$

Future volume counterfactual:

$$
p(Q_2 \mid do(Q_1)).
$$

Identification of follow-up impact:

$$
p(\Delta P_2 \mid do(Q_2), do(Q_1=0))
=
\int p(\Delta P_2 \mid Q_2,Q_1=0,\alpha_1,\alpha_2)
p(\alpha_1,\alpha_2)d\alpha_1d\alpha_2.
$$

Alpha autocorrelation is naively identifiable:

$$
p(\alpha_2 \mid do(\alpha_1=0))
=
p(\alpha_2 \mid \alpha_1=0).
$$

Future volume can be identified by conditioning on either alpha:

$$
p(Q_2 \mid do(Q_1))
=
\int p(Q_2 \mid Q_1,\alpha_1)p(\alpha_1)d\alpha_1,
$$

$$
p(Q_2 \mid do(Q_1))
=
\int p(Q_2 \mid Q_1,\alpha_2)p(\alpha_2)d\alpha_2,
$$

or

$$
p(Q_2 \mid do(Q_1))
=
\int p(Q_2 \mid Q_1,\alpha_1,\alpha_2)p(\alpha_1,\alpha_2)d\alpha_1d\alpha_2.
$$

### Main result

Follow-up impact requires controlling for both alphas. Alpha autocorrelation is naively identifiable. Future volume is identifiable by controlling for alpha.

### Interpretation

As in prediction bias, alpha is the critical confounder for price impact. The new complication is temporal dependence between orders.

