## 6.7 Concluding Thoughts

### Purpose

Explain the broader organizational value of causal inference in trading.

### Setup / formulation

The chapter identifies three broader applications:

- Causal graphs measure and reduce trading-infrastructure complexity.
- Causal graphs improve live experiment design.
- Causal graphs improve simulated trading.

A complex trading infrastructure is one in which fewer clean actions and counterfactuals can be measured or enacted.

### Main result

Causal inference is not only a technical correction for biased estimators. It is also a design framework for trading systems, simulations, and stakeholder communication.

### Interpretation

Traders often want optionality and manual intervention. Developers often want simpler systems with fewer moving parts. Causal graphs provide a way to evaluate system design by asking which counterfactuals remain measurable.

