## Key formulas to preserve

Prediction-bias pedagogical regressions:

$$
\Delta P = \lambda f(Q) + \epsilon.
$$

$$
\Delta P = \alpha + \lambda f(Q) + \epsilon.
$$

Prediction bias:

$$
E[\Delta P \mid do(Q)] \neq E[\Delta P \mid Q].
$$

Alpha counterfactual:

$$
p(\Delta P \mid do(Q=0),\alpha)
=
p(\Delta P \mid Q=0,\alpha).
$$

Impact counterfactual under Simpson’s trading graph:

$$
p(\Delta P \mid do(Q))
=
\int p(\Delta P \mid Q,\alpha)p(\alpha)d\alpha.
$$

Historical-alpha impact regression:

$$
\Delta P = \Delta I(\lambda,Q) + \beta \alpha_{\text{historical}} + \epsilon.
$$

Unperturbed returns:

$$
\Delta S = \Delta P - \Delta I(\lambda,Q).
$$

New alpha regression:

$$
\Delta S = \beta^n \alpha_{\text{new}} + \epsilon'.
$$

Ridge impact model:

$$
\lambda_\theta
=
\arg\min_\lambda
\left\{
\|\Delta P - \Delta I(\lambda,Q)\|^2
+
\theta \|\lambda\|^2
\right\}.
$$

Synchronization impact with leakage:

$$
p(\Delta P \mid do(Q))
=
\int p(\Delta P \mid Q,\alpha)p(\alpha)d\alpha.
$$

Synchronization impact without leakage:

$$
p(\Delta P \mid do(Q),do(M))
=
\int p(\Delta P \mid Q,M,\alpha)p(\alpha)d\alpha.
$$

External impact:

$$
p(\Delta P \mid do(M))
=
\int p(\Delta P \mid M,Q,\alpha)p(Q,\alpha)dQd\alpha.
$$

Leakage:

$$
p(M \mid do(Q))
=
\int p(M \mid Q,\alpha)p(\alpha)d\alpha.
$$

Crowding:

$$
p(M \mid do(Q=0),\alpha)
=
p(M \mid Q=0,\alpha).
$$

Anonymity assumption:

$$
\forall q \in \mathbb{R},
\quad
p(\Delta P \mid do(M=q),do(Q=0))
=
p(\Delta P \mid do(M=0),do(Q=q)).
$$

Implicit microstructure impact:

$$
p(\Delta P \mid do(Q))
=
\int p(\Delta P \mid Q,\alpha)p(\alpha)d\alpha.
$$

Explicit microstructure impact:

$$
p(\Delta P \mid do(Q^r))
=
\int p(\Delta P \mid Q^r,\alpha,\alpha^{LL})
p(\alpha,\alpha^{LL})d\alpha d\alpha^{LL}.
$$

Implementation bias:

$$
p(\Delta P \mid do(Q^r))
\neq
\int p(\Delta P \mid Q^r,\alpha=x)p(\alpha=x)dx.
$$

Implementation transfer-learning penalty:

$$
\theta \|\lambda^i - \lambda^e\|^2.
$$

Issuer bias:

$$
E[\Delta P_2 \mid do(Q_2),do(Q_1=0)]
\neq
E[\Delta P_2 \mid Q_2,Q_1=0].
$$

Follow-up impact:

$$
p(\Delta P_2 \mid do(Q_2),do(Q_1=0))
=
\int p(\Delta P_2 \mid Q_2,Q_1=0,\alpha_1,\alpha_2)
p(\alpha_1,\alpha_2)d\alpha_1d\alpha_2.
$$

Alpha autocorrelation:

$$
p(\alpha_2 \mid do(\alpha_1=0))
=
p(\alpha_2 \mid \alpha_1=0).
$$

Future volume:

$$
p(Q_2 \mid do(Q_1))
=
\int p(Q_2 \mid Q_1,\alpha_1)p(\alpha_1)d\alpha_1.
$$

$$
p(Q_2 \mid do(Q_1))
=
\int p(Q_2 \mid Q_1,\alpha_2)p(\alpha_2)d\alpha_2.
$$

$$
p(Q_2 \mid do(Q_1))
=
\int p(Q_2 \mid Q_1,\alpha_1,\alpha_2)
p(\alpha_1,\alpha_2)d\alpha_1d\alpha_2.
$$

Random-sign sequence result:

$$
p(Q_2 \mid do(Q_1)) = p(Q_2 \mid Q_1).
$$

Issuer smoothing penalty:

$$
\theta \|\lambda_2 - \lambda_1\|^2.
$$

Multi-period smoothing penalty:

$$
\theta \sum_t \|\lambda_{t+1} - \lambda_t\|^2.
$$

